President Muhammadu Buhari will be address Nigerians on Monday (today) at 8pm. The Senior special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Mr. Garba Shehu, announced  this in his Facebook page on Monday “President Muhammadu Buhari will address the nation Monday, April 27, 2020 at 8pm. “Television, radio and other electronic media stations are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively for the broadcast. This will be the third time President Buhari would be addressing Nigerians since the COVID-19 Pandemic got to the country. His last address was two weeks ago, when he extended the lockdown order of Lagos, FCT and Ogun states in a bid to curtail the spread of COVID-19 in the country.